Jae,

The usual list ahead of January 15. If you can get me a clean pack by
January 10, 2027 we can finish the meeting in 90 minutes instead of
three hours.

What I need staged:

  1. Receivables aged through end of December 2026, by bucket
     (0-30 / 31-60 / 61-90 / 90+), with notes on any I should treat
     as collection-risk.

  2. Equipment loan amortization tied out against the bank balance.
     Your prior year-end carry was a round number, so confirm the
     current principal from the most recent statement and not from
     QuickBooks if the two disagree.

  3. SEP-IRA contribution totals for the year and the running balance.

  4. Payments-received by channel - Stripe, Square, PayPal - reconciled
     into QuickBooks. We will revisit the bookkeeping treatment for
     transaction fees if the channel mix shifts materially.

  5. A short note on the apprentice-hours payroll picture so I can
     calibrate the employer credit on Jake.

If anything is in flight - hires, large equipment, the solar service
expansion - drop me a heads-up before the meeting so I am not learning
about it in the room.

Talk in January.

